This paper focuses on improving the robustness of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) against adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a novel method of convolution, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the security aspect of CNNs, which could be classified under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses extensive experiments to evaluate the proposed method, which could be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
